---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Recommendations"
  description="Books, resources, and tools recommended by Leaf for developers, tech leads, and anyone interested in human skills and better ways of working."
>
  <main class="recommendations-page">
    <h1 class="page-title">Things I recommend</h1>

    <p class="intro">Stuff I mention a lot.</p>

    <section class="rec-section">
      <h2>What I do</h2>
      <ul class="list-arrow">
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.artomat.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Art-o-mat</a> –
          I've sold a few hundred tiny pieces of art through this.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://thebookacademy.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >The Book Academy</a
          >{' '}
          – I'm a graduate. Luvvie Ajayi Jones is wonderful.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://bouncingleaf.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >bouncingleaf.com</a
          > – My art site
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://prisonbookprogram.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Prison Book Program
          </a>{' '}
          – I volunteer there once or twice a month. If you have books{' '}
          <a
            href="https://prisonbookprogram.org/donate-books/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            meeting their criteria
          </a>
          , you can give them to me to donate!
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="rec-section">
      <h2>Books</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        Books I've read and highly recommend. The{' '}
        <a
          href="https://bookshop.org/shop/beyond-writing-code"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          bookshop.org
        </a>{' '}
        links are affiliate links. Support independent bookstores!
      </p>

      <h3>Tech books include:</h3>
      <ul class="list-arrow">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://itrevolution.com/product/accelerate/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Accelerate: Building and Scaling High Performing Technology Organizations
          </a>{' '}
          by Dr. Nicole Forsgren, Jez Humble, and Gene Kim.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://itrevolution.com/product/the-phoenix-project/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            The Phoenix Project
          </a>{' '}
          by Gene Kim, Kevin Behr, and George Spafford. A fictional account of a DevOps transformation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/observability-engineering/9781492076438/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Observability Engineering
          </a>{' '}
          by Charity Majors, Liz Fong-Jones, and George Miranda. THE book to read about observability.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/the-staff-engineers/9781098118723/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            The Staff Engineer's Path
          </a>{' '}
          by Tanya Reilly. What's beyond Senior Developer?
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://bookshop.org/a/114662/9781966280026"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Vibe Coding
          </a>{' '}
          by Gene Kim and Steve Yegge.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.janelleshane.com/book-you-look-like-a-thing"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            You Look Like a Thing and I Love You
          </a>{' '}
          by Janelle Shane. Super accessible. I recommend this to anyone curious about machine learning
          and AI, regardless of their existing knowledge on the topic.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Leadership and other books:</h3>
      <ul class="list-arrow">
        <li>Brené Brown – not sure you can go wrong with any of her books.</li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://us.macmillan.com/books/9781250184726/extremeownership/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Extreme Ownership
          </a>{' '}
          by Jocko Willink and Leif Babin
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.jimcollins.com/books.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Good to Great
          </a>{' '}
          by Jim Collins. The most engaging audiobook narrator I've ever heard.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://luvvie.org/books/professional-troublemaker/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Professional Troublemaker
          </a>{' '}
          (or really any{' '}
          <a href="https://luvvie.org/books/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">book</a>) by
          Luvvie Ajayi Jones.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://simonsinek.com/books/start-with-why/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Start With Why
          </a>{' '}
          by Simon Sinek. I was skeptical, Sinek seems trendy. But by the time I'd read the first few
          chapters, I was a fan.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://davidmarquet.com/books/turn-the-ship-around-book/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Turn the Ship Around!
          </a>{' '}
          by L. David Marquet. Why bottom-up leadership beats top-down, even on a nuclear submarine.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.wrongfitrightfit.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Wrong Fit, Right Fit
          </a>{' '}
          by Dr. André Martin. It's not always about good vs. bad company culture.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="rec-section">
      <h2>Where I get books</h2>
      <p>
        Support your indie bookstores! And don't forget your public library, they have audio books
        and ebooks too!
      </p>
      <ul class="list-arrow">
        <li>
          Physical copies:{' '}
          <a
            href="https://bookshop.org/shop/beyond-writing-code"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Bookshop.org
          </a>{' '}
          (more recommendations listed there!)
        </li>
        <li>
          Audio books: <a href="http://libro.fm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >libro.fm</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="rec-section">
      <h2>Tech resources</h2>
      <ul class="list-arrow">
        <li>
          <a href="https://videos.itrevolution.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Enterprise Technology Leadership Summit videos
          </a>
          , including{' '}
          <a
            href="https://videos.itrevolution.com/watch/1002122769"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            my 2024 talk
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://leaddev.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LeadDev</a> – good
          articles and videos from past conferences.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.aiweirdness.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >AI Weirdness</a
          > – researcher Janelle Shane
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="rec-section">
      <h2>Interesting articles, podcasts, posts</h2>
      <ul class="list-arrow">
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.noidea.dog/glue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Being Glue</a
          >, by Tanya Reilly
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://blog.fsck.com/2025/05/28/dear-diary-the-user-asked-me-if-im-alive/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Dear diary, today the user asked me if I'm alive
          </a>
          , by Jesse Vincent
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/dare-to-lead-with-bren%C3%A9-brown/id1730985049?i=1000654901562"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Dr. Joy Buolamwini on Unmasking AI
          </a>
          , with Brené Brown
        </li>
        <li>
          The weekly <a href="https://luvvie.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >LuvvLetter</a
          >, by Luvvie Ajayi Jones. Rants, reflections, and recommendations. My favorite of the
          newsletters I receive.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/own-your-impact/id1807445068"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Own your Impact
          </a>
          , by Macy Robison
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="rec-section">
      <h2>Artists</h2>
      <p>Here are some artists whose work I enjoy:</p>
      <ul class="list-arrow">
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://wardfdn.org/artists/larry-barth/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Larry Barth
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://rosemarymosco.com/comics/bird-and-moon"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Bird and Moon
          </a>{' '}
          by Rosemary Mosco
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.instagram.com/birdstrips/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Birdstrips
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a
            href="https://www.instagram.com/chuckdrawsthings/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Chuck Draws Things
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.falseknees.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >False Knees</a
          > by Joshua Barkman
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.milkywayopera.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Milky Way Opera
          </a>{' '}
          by Jenny Johannesson
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="affiliate-disclosure">
      <hr />
      <p>
        Book-related links above are "affiliate links" with a special tracking code. If you click on
        an affiliate link and purchase the item, I will receive a commission. The price of the item
        is the same whether through an affiliate link or not.
      </p>
      <p>
        I only recommend products or services which I use myself and believe will add value for my
        readers.
      </p>
      <p>
        By using the affiliate links, you are helping support my work, and I genuinely appreciate
        your support.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .recommendations-page {
    max-width: var(--content-max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
  }

  .intro {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-gray);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .rec-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .section-intro {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    color: var(--color-gray);
  }

  .section-intro a {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .list-arrow {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .list-arrow li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .list-arrow li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent-teal);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .affiliate-disclosure {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-gray);
  }

  .affiliate-disclosure hr {
    display: none;
  }

  .affiliate-disclosure p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-accent-teal);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
